The paper deals with an algorithmic problem related to graph theory and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of the fast zeta transform and inclusion-exclusion principle indicates that it could be related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The problem of channel assignment is also relevant to network infrastructure (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes improvements to algorithms for special cases, which suggests that it could be related to algorithms (cs.AL) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
